# Domain structure

Organize by **bounded context** (business language), not by technical layer.

## Packages

| Path | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `packages/shared` | Permissions, plans, roles, nav, shared types only |
| `packages/database` | Prisma schema, migrations, seed |
| `apps/api/src/{context}/` | Nest feature module per domain |
| `src/` (web) | Routes, components, `@/` API clients |

## Naming

- API files: `{context}` or `{context}-{aggregate}` prefix, role suffix last (`.service.ts`, `.controller.ts`, `.repositories.ts`, `.dto.ts`, `.spec.ts`).
- Web: domain UI in `components/{context}/`, helpers in `lib/{context}/` or `lib/api/`, routes stay URL-shaped.
- Web imports use `@/` absolute paths. Same-context API imports use `./`; cross-context use `../other-context/`.

## Placement

- New tenant feature → API module under `apps/api/src/<context>/`, shared permissions, web routes + `lib/`, isolation tests.
- Platform-only → `platform/` + `/admin` routes, never mixed into tenant modules.
- No god `utils/` files; keep helpers next to their context.

Use the `velon-domain-structure`, `domain-driven-design`, and `clean-ddd-hexagonal` skills when adding or moving modules.
